  Centered Content Section:
  - Contains various elements including a title, price, image, quantity selector, add to cart button, and a link.

  Structure:
  - The centered content section is enclosed within a <div> element with a class of "centerContent".
  - It consists of the following elements:

  Title:
  - The title is represented by an <h1> element with an ID of "item".
  - The content of the title is dynamically rendered using the variable "myMessage".

  Price:
  - The price is represented by an <h2> element with an ID of "price".
  - The content of the price is dynamically rendered using the variable "price".

  Image:
  - The image is represented by an <img> element with a src attribute pointing to the image file.
  - The image source is dynamically rendered using the variable "myImage".
  - It has a width of "180px".

  Quantity Selector:
  - The quantity selector is represented by a <select> element with an ID of "quantity" and a name of "quantity".
  - It contains multiple <option> elements representing different quantity options.
  - The default quantity is set to "1" using the "selected" attribute.

  Add to Cart Button:
  - The "Add to Cart" button is represented by a <button> element with a class of "add-to-cart".
  - It triggers the "addToCart()" function when clicked.

  Link:
  - The link is represented by an <a> element with an href attribute pointing to the "home" page.
  - It provides a link to navigate back to the home page.

  The dynamic values ("<%=myMessage%>", "<%=price%>", "<%=myImage%>") are  provided by a server-side EJS rendering .
-->
    <div class="centerContent">
      <h1 id="item">
        <%=myMessage%>
      </h1>
      <h2 id="price">Price: <%=price%>
      </h2>
      <img src="img/<%= myImage%>" width="180px">
